---
title: Radio Button List
---

p.-text
  | Radio button lists are used to wrap a series of radio buttons on a list.

h3 Examples
h4 Base
p.-text To render a series of radio buttons in a list, apply the class <code>m-listGroup</code> in a list.
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    h5 Select an option
    ul.m-listGroup(style="max-width:20rem")
      li.m-formGroup
        input(type="radio", class="a-input", name="radiobuttonList", id="radio1")
        label(for="radio1")
        label.-text(for="radio1") Option 1
      li.m-formGroup
        input(type="radio", class="a-input", name="radiobuttonList", id="radio2")
        label(for="radio2")
        label.-text(for="radio2") Option 2
      li.m-formGroup
        input(type="radio", class="a-input", name="radiobuttonList", id="radio3")
        label(for="radio3")
        label.-text(for="radio3") Option 3
      li.m-formGroup
        input(type="radio", class="a-input", name="radiobuttonList", id="radio4")
        label(for="radio4")
        label.-text(for="radio4") Option 4
      li.m-formGroup
        input(type="radio", class="a-input", name="radiobuttonList", id="radio5")
        label(for="radio5")
        label.-text(for="radio5") Option 5
